name: language_sql_data_single_quote
description: |
  A lone apostrophe terminates a naively interpolated SQL string literal. It
  should survive parameter binding as ordinary data and is the smallest useful
  canary for missing or incorrect SQL string escaping.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
pair:
  - with: doubled-single-quote.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "language"
  - "sql"
  - "sql-data"
  - "string"
  - "single-quote"
  - "escaping"
  - "parameter-binding"
  - "injection-canary"
---
'
